OData: acronym for Open Data Protocol
Protocol: set of rules
Data: collection of information
Open: open means any one can come in and go out i.e.
It is an open standard that can be consumed by any application, program, software or device of any SAP or Non-SAP world

-> The OData protocol is HTTP based, any programming language with HTTP stack can be used for consumung OData services.
-> In simple words we can say OData is a web protocol which is used for unlocking and sharing data. 
-> With OData any SAP or Non-SAP applications they can talk to each other and can share information.

